{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":866,"text":"As a little Hawaiian,"},{"time":2095,"text":"my mom and auntie always told me\nstories about Kalaupapa --"},{"time":5501,"text":"the Hawaiian leper colony"},{"time":6846,"text":"surrounded by the highest\nsea cliffs in the world --"},{"time":9697,"text":"and Father Damien,"},{"time":11133,"text":"the Belgian missionary who gave his life\nfor the Hawaiian community."},{"time":15102,"text":"As a young nurse,"},{"time":16489,"text":"my aunt trained the nuns\ncaring for the remaining lepers"},{"time":19454,"text":"almost a 100 years after\nFather Damien died of leprosy."},{"time":24501,"text":"I remember stories she told"},{"time":26196,"text":"about traveling down\nswitchback cliff paths on a mule,"},{"time":29172,"text":"while my uncle played\nher favorite hula songs on the ukulele"},{"time":32327,"text":"all the way down to Kalaupapa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34730,"text":"You see, as a youngster,"},{"time":36255,"text":"I was always curious about a few things."},{"time":38681,"text":"First was why a Belgian missionary\nchose to live in complete isolation"},{"time":43755,"text":"in Kalaupapa,"},{"time":44969,"text":"knowing he would inevitably\ncontract leprosy"},{"time":47223,"text":"from the community of people\nhe sought to help."},{"time":50256,"text":"And secondly,"},{"time":52617,"text":"where did the leprosy bacteria come from?"},{"time":55002,"text":"And why were KƒÅnaka Maoli,"},{"time":56781,"text":"the indigenous people of Hawaii,"},{"time":59054,"text":"so susceptible to developing\nleprosy, or \"mai Pake?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":63853,"text":"This got my curious about what\nmakes us unique as Hawaiians --"},{"time":67607,"text":"namely, our genetic makeup."},{"time":70964,"text":"But it wasn't until high school,"},{"time":72932,"text":"through the Human Genome Project,"},{"time":74568,"text":"that I realized I wasn't alone"},{"time":76791,"text":"in trying to connect\nour unique genetic ancestry"},{"time":79643,"text":"to our potential health,\nwellness and illness."},{"time":84061,"text":"You see,"},{"time":85235,"text":"the 2.7 billion-dollar project"},{"time":87058,"text":"promised an era of predictive\nand preventative medicine"},{"time":91072,"text":"based on our unique genetic makeup."},{"time":93849,"text":"So to me it always seemed obvious"},{"time":95549,"text":"that in order to achieve this dream,"},{"time":98301,"text":"we would need to sequence\na diverse cohort of people"},{"time":102338,"text":"to obtain the full spectrum\nof human genetic variation on the planet."},{"time":106303,"text":"That's why 10 years later,"},{"time":108899,"text":"it continues to shock me,"},{"time":110597,"text":"knowing that 96 percent of genome studies"},{"time":113835,"text":"associating common genetic variation\nwith specific diseases"},{"time":117439,"text":"have focused exclusively\non individuals of European ancestry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122069,"text":"Now you don't need a PhD"},{"time":123502,"text":"to see that that leaves four percent\nfor the rest of diversity."},{"time":127164,"text":"And in my own searching,"},{"time":129316,"text":"I've discovered that far less\nthan one percent"},{"time":131849,"text":"have actually focused on indigenous\ncommunities, like myself."},{"time":135481,"text":"So that begs the question:"},{"time":137552,"text":"Who is the Human Genome\nProject actually for?"},{"time":140853,"text":"Just like we have\ndifferent colored eyes and hair,"},{"time":143235,"text":"we metabolize drugs differently"},{"time":144767,"text":"based on the variation in our genomes."},{"time":146978,"text":"So how many of you\nwould be shocked to learn"},{"time":150439,"text":"that 95 percent of clinical trials"},{"time":153245,"text":"have also exclusively featured\nindividuals of European ancestry?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":158387,"text":"This bias"},{"time":159746,"text":"and systematic lack of engagement\nof indigenous people"},{"time":163611,"text":"in both clinical trials\nand genome studies"},{"time":166619,"text":"is partially the result\nof a history of distrust."},{"time":170893,"text":"For example,"},{"time":172067,"text":"in 1989, researchers\nfrom Arizona State University"},{"time":176020,"text":"obtained blood samples\nfrom Arizona's Havasupai tribe,"},{"time":179610,"text":"promising to alleviate the burden\nof type 2 diabetes"},{"time":182568,"text":"that was plaguing their community,"},{"time":184452,"text":"only to turn around and use\nthose exact same samples --"},{"time":188361,"text":"without the Havasupai's consent --"},{"time":190088,"text":"to study rates\nof schizophrenia, inbreeding,"},{"time":193617,"text":"and challenge\nthe Havasupai's origin story."},{"time":197319,"text":"When the Havasupai found out,"},{"time":199885,"text":"they sued successfully for $700,000,"},{"time":203102,"text":"and they banned ASU from conducting\nresearch on their reservation."},{"time":208961,"text":"This culminated in a sort of domino effect"},{"time":212239,"text":"with local tribes in the Southwest --"},{"time":214025,"text":"including the Navajo Nation,"},{"time":215478,"text":"one of the largest\ntribes in the country --"},{"time":217589,"text":"putting a moratorium on genetic research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219860,"text":"Now despite this history of distrust,"},{"time":222765,"text":"I still believe that indigenous people\ncan benefit from genetic research."},{"time":227264,"text":"And if we don't do something soon,"},{"time":229533,"text":"the gap in health disparities\nis going to continue to widen."},{"time":233113,"text":"Hawaii, for example,"},{"time":234542,"text":"has the longest life expectancy\non average of any state in the US,"},{"time":238273,"text":"yet native Hawaiians like myself"},{"time":241154,"text":"die a full decade\nbefore our non-native counterparts,"},{"time":244264,"text":"because we have some\nof the highest rates of type 2 diabetes,"},{"time":248339,"text":"obesity,"},{"time":249514,"text":"and the number one and number\ntwo killers in the US:"},{"time":252063,"text":"cardiovascular disease and cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253926,"text":"So how do we ensure"},{"time":255669,"text":"the populations of people\nthat need genome sequencing the most"},{"time":258844,"text":"are not the last to benefit?"},{"time":260671,"text":"My vision is to make\ngenetic research more native,"},{"time":265418,"text":"to indigenize genome\nsequencing technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268902,"text":"Traditionally, genomes\nare sequenced in laboratories."},{"time":272555,"text":"Here's an image of your classic\ngenome sequencer."},{"time":275167,"text":"It's huge."},{"time":276342,"text":"It's the size of a refrigerator."},{"time":278750,"text":"There's this obvious physical limitation."},{"time":281321,"text":"But what if you could sequence\ngenomes on the fly?"},{"time":285210,"text":"What if you could fit a genome\nsequencer in your pocket?"},{"time":291848,"text":"This nanopore-based sequencer"},{"time":294270,"text":"is one 10,000th the size\nof your traditional genome sequencer."},{"time":298779,"text":"It doesn't have the same\nphysical limitations,"},{"time":301024,"text":"in that it's not tethered to a lab bench\nwith extraneous cords,"},{"time":305324,"text":"large vats of chemicals\nor computer monitors."},{"time":308456,"text":"It allows us to de-black box genome\nsequencing technology development"},{"time":313631,"text":"in a way that's immersive\nand collaborative,"},{"time":316267,"text":"activating and empowering\nindigenous communities ..."},{"time":320476,"text":"as citizen scientists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323092,"text":"100 years later in Kalaupapa,"},{"time":325672,"text":"we now have the technology to sequence\nleprosy bacteria in real time,"},{"time":329935,"text":"using mobile genome sequencers,"},{"time":332847,"text":"remote access to the Internet"},{"time":335880,"text":"and cloud computation."},{"time":338440,"text":"But only if that's what\nHawaiian people want."},{"time":342074,"text":"In our space,"},{"time":343394,"text":"on our terms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346367,"text":"IndiGenomics is about science\nfor the people by the people."},{"time":352196,"text":"We'll be starting with a tribal\nconsultation resource,"},{"time":356165,"text":"focused on educating\nindigenous communities"},{"time":359400,"text":"on the potential use and misuse\nof genetic information."},{"time":362861,"text":"Eventually we'd like to have our own\nIndiGenomics research institute"},{"time":366195,"text":"to conduct our own experiments"},{"time":367648,"text":"and educate the next generation\nof indigenous scientists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371523,"text":"In the end,"},{"time":373108,"text":"indigenous people need to be partners in\nand not subjects of genetic research."},{"time":378179,"text":"And for those on the outside,"},{"time":380156,"text":"just as Father Damien did,"},{"time":382625,"text":"the research community needs\nto immerse itself in indigenous culture"},{"time":387007,"text":"or die trying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388984,"text":"Mahalo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390213,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}